Directional OW3D initial-condition batch
Updated: 16-Mar-2026 01:11:20

Purpose
Generate directional OW3D cases to measure how quickly the error wave separates from the main wave group.

What this batch is trying to verify
- Each case starts from an early MF12 initialization time and is marched to a common end time of +5Tp relative to focus.
- The t_init sweep is intended to show when the error wave becomes clearly separated from the dominant wave group.
- Each subdirectory is a runnable OW3D case and is named so different start times remain easy to compare during postprocessing.

Current workflow
- Direct MF12 reconstruction up to order 2 for each requested phase.
- Reuse the phase=0 third-order increment by applying a 3phi shift for the non-zero phase cases.
- Surface-only OW3D output; no kinematic export.
- One subdirectory per generated case.

Current settings snapshot
- output directory = directional initial condition/error_wave_separation
- phases = [0, 90, 180, 270] deg
- heading = 0.0 deg
- spread = 15.0 deg
- t_init sweep = [-40] Tp
- target end time = 5.00 Tp
- domain = [9008.151, 3378.057] m
- grid = [1025, 257], dx = 8.788 m, dy = 13.144 m
- surface stride = 4
